That's what you get, if you've turned off uploading or set it very low, or maybe you don't have an open port for the torrent client to recieve upload requests on.
Another possibility might be a slow internet connection, especially an upload speed like 256 Kbps or less. (Please notice that KByte/s and Kbit/s is not the same).
Check your router.
If it's that low, and you should have a higher upload to your ISP, per your subscription, tell customer service about it.
